summary:
Requested by @balanced-ram
The night was perfect. Carol was able to find the perfect hill for the two of you to look at the...
body:
Requested by @balanced-ram

The night was perfect. Carol was able to find the perfect hill for the two of you to look at the stars on. So now here you found yourselves laying on the blanket as the lights in the sky glittered above you. For the past little while you’ve been rambling on about constellation and pointing them out to Carol when you could. Carol wasn’t ignoring you exactly but she was so in awe of you that your voice sounded like an echo from far away.

Eventually your magnificence was too much for Carol. Right in the middle of your sentence about the Big Dipper, Carol cut in. “Will you just marry me already?” The woman asked, voice ever so casually. How easily her question left her lips took you off guard. You honestly weren’t sure if she was joking or not. So when you made an effort to reply your voice came out shaky and unsure.

“W-what?” You laughed. You expected Carol to tell you that she was kidding, but she simply continued to smile at you and stare at you with those sparkling eyes of hers. “Wait, are you serious? Not to say that I’d say no if you asked of course b-but do you mean that?”. Carol chuckled before leaning over to kiss you.

“Of course I mean it”.

REQUESTS ARE OPEN
